    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>cauliflower</strong> into small florets and cut the stem[s] into bite-sized pieces (discard the leaves)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped cauliflower</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-22 min or until tender and golden</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>orzo</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the orzo for 6-8 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the orzo and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and cook, stirring often, for 3-4 or until golden brown</p><p>Once golden brown, remove from the heat and add 1/3 of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and your <strong>crispy onions</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>herby crumb</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cannellini beans </strong>(no need to drain!) with all the<strong> bean water </strong>to the pot with the cooked orzo</p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> with your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>umami seasoning</strong>,<strong> grated cheese</strong>,<strong> remaining parsley </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Return to a low heat, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until the cheese is melted and everything is warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>roast cauliflower florets</strong> to the pot and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>cauliflower cheese bean & orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-bean-and-orzo-bowl-with-herby-crumbs/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cauliflower cheese bean and & orzo </strong>topped with the <strong>herby crumb</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
